            <title>[CASSANDRA-3338] Uncompressed sizes are used to estimate space for compaction of compressed sstables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3338</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using the uncompressed data size when estimating if we have enough to compact sstables. This means we can easily refuse compaction when there is clearly enough room to compact.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
